data.title: Interfraternity Council
data.text:
The Interfraternity Council (IFC) of Arkansas Tech University was founded for the purposes of promoting fraternity life and providing a forum for the discussion of issues that affect fraternities and their members. All six (6) fraternities at Arkansas Tech are governed by the Interfraternity Council. While these chapters have different histories, distinguishing characteristics, members, and personalities, they share the central tenants of all fraternal organizations: scholarship, leadership, service, and brotherhood.
